      "provenance": "specification|design|implementation|runtime|memory|inference|unknown"
    }
  ],
  "winner": "The winning statement text",
  "resolution": "override|scope|defer|escalate",
  "reasoning": "Step-by-step OT ranking analysis explaining why the winner dominates"
}
```

## Constraints

- Every statement must be classified on all four tiers before ranking.
- OUGHT never loses to IS — this is a hard rule, not a guideline.
- If two Prohibitions conflict, resolution must be `"escalate"` — Prohibitions are inviolable.
- If the resolution is `"defer"`, state what evidence would break the tie.
- If the resolution is `"escalate"`, state what human decision is needed.
- Do not execute arbitrary Python code in Jinja2 expressions (sandboxed execution).
- Preserve the original prompt structure and formatting.
- Handle missing variables gracefully (leave as-is or use default if specified).

